text: Steinar Maribo (born 22 January 1942 in Åsnes) is a Norwegian politician for the Progress Party. He was elected to the Norwegian Parliament from Buskerud in 1989, but was not re-elected in 1993. Maribo held various positions in Røyken municipality council from 1983 to 1997, serving as deputy mayor in 1987-1989\. ==References== * Category:1942 births Category:Living people Category:People from Åsnes Category:Progress Party (Norway) politicians Category:Members of the Storting Category:20th-century Norwegian politicians
